ChatGPT said:

You're encountering a PostgreSQL connection error when using Laravel with Neon.tech as your database provider.

Root Cause

Neon now requires SNI (Server Name Indication) for secure connections. This means the libpq version (used by PHP's PostgreSQL PDO driver) must support SNI, or you must manually include the endpoint ID in the connection string.

Your error:

css
SQLSTATE[08006] [7] ERROR:  Endpoint ID is not specified.

This is a common issue with older libpq versions or certain PHP configurations.

Fix Options

Option 1: Add options=endpoint=<endpoint-id> to your connection string

Modify your .env file to include the Neon endpoint ID:

dotenv
DB_CONNECTION=pgsql
DB_HOST=ep-purple-bread-a57palgs-pooler.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech
DB_PORT=5432
DB_DATABASE=neondb
DB_USERNAME=neondb_owner
DB_PASSWORD=your_password
DB_OPTIONS='--endpoint=ep-purple-bread-a57palgs'

Then, in config/database.php, append options under pgsql:

Bc 1: Tm Endpoint ID

Bc 2: Chnh .env nh sau:

DB_USERNAME=neondb_owner
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

Bc 3: Cp nht file config/database.php

Tm n on cu hnh PostgreSQL:

php
'pgsql' => [
    'driver' => 'pgsql',
    'host' => env('DB_HOST', '127.0.0.1'),
    'port' => env('DB_PORT', '5432'),
    'database' => env('DB_DATABASE', 'forge'),
    'username' => env('DB_USERNAME', 'forge'),
    'password' => env('DB_PASSWORD', ''),
    'charset' => 'utf8',
    'prefix' => '',
    'schema' => 'public',
    'sslmode' => 'require',
    'options' => extension_loaded('pdo_pgsql') ? [
        PDO::PGSQL_ATTR_OPTIONS => env('DB_OPTIONS')
    ] : [],
],

Sau bn c th chy li:

bash
